    callForPapers:
      '&lt;h2>&lt;strong>Call for Papers: 28th Global Conference on Strategic Management and Planning (GCSMP)&lt;/strong>&lt;/h2>&lt;ul>&lt;li>&lt;span style="color: rgb(75, 79, 88);">We are excited to invite submissions for the 28th Global Conference on Strategic Management and Planning, scheduled to be held in Vancouver, Canada. This upcoming international conference in Canada unites a rich mix of academics, industry experts, consultants, and practitioners to explore and share the latest research and innovative strategies in strategic management. We welcome submissions that promote collaboration, challenge conventional views, and introduce innovative approaches to strategic management dynamics. Each paper will go through an extensive double-blind peer review process, ensuring the highest standards of academic and professional integrity. The future of strategic management depends on your contributions. We look forward to your insightful research, which will undoubtedly shape future trends and practices.&nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;strong style="color: rgb(214, 34, 41);">Topics of interest include, but are not limited to:&lt;/strong>Strategic Analysis and Decision-Making&lt;/li>&lt;li>Leadership and Organizational Behavior in Strategy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Environmental Scanning and Industry Analysis&lt;/li>&lt;li>Corporate Governance and Ethics in Strategy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Resource Allocation and Strategic Resource Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Performance Measurement and Balanced Scorecards&lt;/li>&lt;li>Innovation and Competitive Strategy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Global Strategy and International Business Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Strategic Change Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Digital Transformation and Technology in Strategic Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Sustainability and CSR in Strategic Planning&lt;/li>&lt;li>Risk Management and Business Continuity Planning&lt;/li>&lt;li>Entrepreneurial Strategies and New Venture Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Strategic Human Resource Management&lt;/li>&lt;li>Corporate Strategy and Business Policy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Crisis Management and Strategy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Mergers and Acquisitions Strategy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Strategic Marketing and Market Positioning&lt;/li>&lt;/ul>&lt;p>&lt;br>&lt;/p>',
