    callForPapers:
      '&lt;h2>&lt;strong>Call for Papers: Global Conference on Gender and Disability Human Rights (GCGDHR)&lt;/strong>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>We are excited to invite submissions for the Global Conference on Gender and Disability Human Rights (GCGDHR), a premier platform for researchers, policymakers, and advocates dedicated to advancing inclusive human rights. This global conference in Australia provides a space to present research, share best practices, and engage in critical discussions on policies and solutions for promoting equality.&lt;/p>&lt;p>We welcome submissions of full papers and abstracts, which will experience a precise double-blind peer review process to ensure high-quality contributions. Selected papers will be featured in the Global Conference Alliance’s online proceedings, providing a platform for global recognition.&lt;/p>&lt;ul>&lt;li>&lt;strong style="color: rgb(214, 34, 41);">Suggested Topics for Submission Include:&lt;/strong>Legal Frameworks and Human Rights Protections for Gender and Disability&lt;/li>&lt;li>Intersectionality and Social Justice in Disability Advocacy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Inclusive Employment Policies and Workplace Diversity&lt;/li>&lt;li>Healthcare Access and Rights for Gender-Diverse and Disabled Individuals&lt;/li>&lt;li>Education, Assistive Technology, and Accessibility in Learning&lt;/li>&lt;li>Gender-Based Violence and Disability: Prevention and Support Strategies&lt;/li>&lt;li>Media Representation and its Impact on Social Perceptions&lt;/li>&lt;li>Public Policy and Legislative Advances for Disability and Gender Rights&lt;/li>&lt;li>Community Engagement and Grassroots Advocacy for Inclusion&lt;/li>&lt;li>Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and Disability Rights&lt;/li>&lt;li>Intersectional Approaches to Gender, Disability, and Race&lt;/li>&lt;li>Mental Health and Disability&lt;/li>&lt;li>Access to Justice for Persons with Disabilities&lt;/li>&lt;li>Disability-Inclusive Urban Planning and Design&lt;/li>&lt;li>The Role of International Organizations in Disability Rights&lt;/li>&lt;li>Disability and Gender in Crisis Situations&lt;/li>&lt;li>Social Media and Disability Advocacy&lt;/li>&lt;li>Youth Empowerment in Disability Rights Movements&lt;/li>&lt;li>Reproductive Rights and Health for Persons with Disabilities&lt;/li>&lt;li>Global Perspectives on Gender and Disability Rights&lt;/li>&lt;/ul>&lt;p>&lt;br>&lt;/p>',
